cultural experience was measured or manipulated, and across samples (Hong Kongers, Jewish Israelis, and U.S.-born Americans). Overall, by integrating the literature on multicultural experiences with that on perceived resource depletion, we demonstrate the state-dependent nature of the advantages of multicultural experiences as well as afford a more nuanced view of the downstream influence of perceived mental depletion. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2018 APA, all rights reserved)","2018-09","2024-01-25 01:03:16","2024-01-25 01:03:16","2024-01-25 01:03:16","445",NA,3,115,NA,"","“The tolerance benefits of multicultural experiences depend on the perception of available mental resources”",NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,"English","",NA,NA,NA,"ProQuest",NA,"Num Pages: 445 Place: Washington, US Publisher: American Psychological Association (US)",NA,"/Users/SchoolAccount/Zotero/storage/X6Q4AJ5S/indicated - 2018 - “The tolerance benefits of multicultural experiences depend on the perception of available mental re.pdf",NA,NA,"Test Construction; Social Psychology (major); Cognitive Control (major); Ingroup Outgroup (major); Multiculturalism (major); Need for Cognition; Prejudice (major)",NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA
